  "text": "We start by giving an overview of our approach, and then describe each step in detail. The first two steps use hashing techniques to compute and store all triplets of angles into hash tables. Geometric hashing techniques were originally devised in the area of computer vision, [CITATION_1] mostly for object recognition applications, and were later applied to several matching problems arising in computational biology. • the name of protein P ; and • the identifier of each SSE of the triplet.",
